---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Mongolia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mongolia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kazakhstan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kazakhstan' },
  { title: 'South Korea for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-korea' },
  { title: 'Japan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/japan' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'mongoliaFit', header: 'Mongolia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MNT$1.5M-2.15M/mo', mongoliaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MNT$1.76M-2.51M/mo', mongoliaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MNT$1.35M-1.93M/mo', mongoliaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MNT$1.26M-1.8M/mo', mongoliaFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MNT$1.35M-2.15M', annual: 'MNT$16.2M-25.8M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MNT$1.85M-2.87M', annual: 'MNT$22.2M-34.4M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MNT$2.49M-3.84M', annual: 'MNT$29.9M-46.1M' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic (UB)', monthly: 'MNT$100K-300K/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Evacuation to Seoul', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'MNT$30M-100M' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mongolia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Mongolia. Vast steppes, nomadic culture, extreme climate, and coverage for adventurous retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mongolia"
  subheadline="Mongolia offers vast steppes, nomadic heritage, Gobi Desert, Buddhist monasteries, and authentic wilderness—an extraordinary adventure destination for hardy, adventurous retirees seeking true frontier experience."
  heroImage="/images/countries/mongolia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Mongolia</h2>
  <p>
    Mongolia offers an utterly unique experience—endless steppes, nomadic ger camps, Gobi Desert, wild horses, Buddhist temples, and authentic frontier culture. For adventurous retirees seeking genuine wilderness and ancient traditions, Mongolia provides experiences unavailable anywhere else. Not for comfort-seekers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Ulaanbaatar ("UB") is capital with 1.5 million people—half the country's population. Healthcare concentrated here. Countryside is vast wilderness. Seoul (2.5 hours) and Beijing (2 hours) provide medical backup. Extreme continental climate: -30°C winters, +30°C summers.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Seoul/Beijing evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Mongolian; Russian, English in UB</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MNT$2M-4M/month (~$600-1,200 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Extreme continental; harsh winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Frontier; nomadic; vast</li>
      <li><strong>Reality check:</strong> Not suitable for most seniors</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Mongolia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Mongolia healthcare is limited—SOS Medica and Intermed Hospital in Ulaanbaatar provide Western-standard care but limited specialists. Public hospitals basic. Outside UB, healthcare is very limited. Complex cases require evacuation to Seoul (2.5-hour flight) with excellent Korean hospitals, or Beijing.
  </p>

  <p>
    Seoul is preferred evacuation destination—Samsung Medical Center, Asan Medical Center are world-class. International insurance with strong Asia-Pacific coverage essential. Don't underestimate medical limitations outside UB.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Seoul Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Seoul is 2.5 hours away with world-class Korean healthcare. Primary evacuation destination for complex cases. Beijing also accessible but Seoul generally preferred. Countryside is extremely remote—medical access may require helicopter. Insurance with strong evacuation coverage critical.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Mongolia visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    30 days visa-free for many nationalities including US, UK, EU. Simple entry.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available through immigration. Various categories for longer stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term residence. Various categories. Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Practical Note</h3>
  <p>
    Few Westerners retire to Mongolia—challenging conditions, extreme climate, limited infrastructure. Primarily for adventure-oriented extended visitors.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Mongolia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Seoul/Beijing coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Remote areas:</strong> Consider helicopter evacuation coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Mongolia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with strong Asia-Pacific coverage essential. Include Seoul and Beijing hospitals. Consider helicopter evacuation for countryside travel. UB has some private care; countryside is extremely remote.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Mongolia, regional evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Mongolia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, Seoul access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Korean hospitals:</strong> World-class backup 2.5 hours away</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation focus:</strong> Critical for frontier destination</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Mongolia with Seoul evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Mongolia (MNT ~3,350 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>UB base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>Seoul network:</strong> World-class backup nearby</li>
    <li><strong>Very affordable living:</strong> Low daily costs offset insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Reality check:</strong> Climate and remoteness challenging</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Adventure Photographer, 65</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month. Extended steppe photography trips. UB base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with helicopter evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MNT$1.5M/month (~$450). Wilderness adventure; Seoul backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Buddhist Scholar, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month. Monastery research. UB and countryside.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MNT$1.8M/month (~$535). Spiritual journey; comprehensive coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Summer Explorer, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Summer only (avoid harsh winter). Nomadic experience.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Asia coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MNT$1.4M/month (~$420). Seasonal adventure; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Mongolia suitable for seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Only for very hardy, adventurous seniors. Extreme climate (-30°C winters), limited healthcare, basic infrastructure outside UB, challenging conditions. Not recommended for those with mobility issues or chronic conditions requiring regular care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are Mongolian winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extreme—Ulaanbaatar is world's coldest capital. January averages -25°C to -30°C. Can drop to -40°C. Pollution from heating coal makes winter air quality poor. Many expats leave for winter months.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's healthcare like outside UB?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very limited—countryside has basic clinics only. Serious emergencies require helicopter evacuation to UB or directly to Seoul. Hours from any medical care in remote areas. Not for those who might need emergency care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why would a senior choose Mongolia?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Unique experience—nowhere else offers endless steppes, nomadic ger camps, wild horses, Gobi Desert. For adventurous souls seeking authentic frontier experience before it's too late. Not for comfort; for lifetime memories.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Mongolia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Mongolia is an extreme destination not suitable for most seniors. Healthcare is very limited outside Ulaanbaatar. Winters are among world's coldest. Only for hardy adventurers with strong evacuation coverage.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
